        "text": "<h2>Off-Road Lights FAQs</h2><h3>1. What are off-road lights used for?</h3><p>Off-road lights improve visibility in dark, rugged, or remote environments where factory headlights fall short.</p><h3>2. Are off-road lights street legal?</h3><p>In many states, off-road lights must be covered or turned off when driving on public roads. Check local laws for compliance.</p><h3>3. What’s the difference between spot and flood beams?</h3><p>Spot beams have a narrow, long-range focus, while flood beams spread light over a wider area for close-up visibility.</p><h3>4. What are the best off-road lights for trucks?</h3><p>Light bars, combo pods, and bumper-mounted floods are popular choices for full-size trucks and Jeeps.</p><h3>5. Do off-road lights drain my battery?</h3><p>High-quality LED lights are energy-efficient, but prolonged use without the engine running can drain the battery.</p><h3>6. Can I install off-road lights myself?</h3><p>Yes, many lights come with plug-and-play wiring harnesses. Basic tools and 12V knowledge are typically all you need.</p><h3>7. How many lumens do I need for off-roading?</h3><p>Anywhere from 2,000 to 20,000 lumens, depending on terrain, speed, and vehicle type.</p><h3>8. What brands of off-road lights do you carry?</h3><p>Strobes N More stocks Feniex, Whelen, and our exclusive SNM Series—designed for rugged performance.</p><h3>9. Do I need a relay for LED off-road lights?</h3><p>Yes, relays protect your wiring and ensure safe, consistent operation of high-power LEDs.</p><h3>10. Where can I buy quality off-road lights online?</h3><p>You can shop premium off-road lights and accessories at<a href=\"https://www.strobesnmore.com\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">strobesnmore.com</span></a> with fast shipping and expert support.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
